text: Raymond Aubrac (31 July 1914 – 10 April 2012) was a French engineer and leader. He was the leader of the French Resistance during the Second World War and a civil engineer after the Second World War. ==Other websites== * * * Category:1914 births Category:2012 deaths Category:French engineers Category:French people of World War II Category:People from Haute-Saône Category:Civil engineers Category:French Resistance
